SIMPLE: inflexibility
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inflexibility
<hw>In*flex"i*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>inflexibilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of
being inflexible, or not capable of being bent or changed; unyielding
stiffness; inflexibleness; rigidity; firmness of will or purpose;
unbending pertinacity; steadfastness; resoluteness; unchangeableness;
obstinacy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>inflexibility</qex> of mechanism.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Baxter.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That grave <qex>inflexibility</qex> of soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Churchill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The purity and <qex>inflexibility</qex> of their faith.</q>
<rj><qau>T. Warton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inflexible</ent>⟦br⟧
